<Task/><Text-field style="Heading 1" layout="Heading 1">Documentation to PointGroups package</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal">PointGroups is a package for in-depth use of point groups.</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Hyperlink linktarget="Help:FiniteGroups" hyperlink="true"><Font underline="true" style="Normal">FiniteGroups</Font></Hyperlink> package is required.</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal">The author is Andriy Zhugayevych, azh@ukr.net.</Text-field>
<Group hide-input="false" labelreference="L58188" drawlabel="true">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">with(FiniteGroups): with(PointGroups):
HT:=LinearAlgebra[HermitianTranspose]:
myRank:=M-&gt;`if`(nops(op(2,M))&gt;0,LinearAlgebra[Rank](M),0):
svf:=[seq(map(FG_simplify,simplify(ReflectionM(map(convert,&lt;sin(Pi/2/n),cos(Pi/2/n),0&gt;,radical)))),n=1..6)]:
unassign('x,y,z,a,b,c');
printf(&quot;Known groups: %{c,}s&quot;,Vector(sort([indices(tbPG,nolist)])));</Text-field>
</Input>
<Output><Text-field style="Line Printed Output" layout="Line Printed Output">Known groups: C,Ch,Ci,Cv,D,Dd,Dh,Di,O,Oh,T,Td,Th,Y,Yh</Text-field>
</Output>
</Group>
